rComments: She is one of the best professors I've met in UofT. Lectures are well organized. Good speaking and handwriting. Materials in exams are very related to your course note. By the way, she is also one of the nicest professors. If you wanna get a reference letter, you probably wanna take her courses.

Good teacher; but one of the hardest courses I've ever taken. Huge difference in difficulty levels between problem sets vs midterms (and i mean huge). Do finish the problem set and think: "yeah, i'm pretty confident about the midterm", but boy will you be wrong. Also, her midterm always include 10 questions to rigorously test basic theories.

Prof Pavel has very organised lectures, but you must keep up with her quick note-writing speed on the blackboard. She wrote her own notes, so you need not any textbook for her courses - aka saving lots of money. However, she likes to test on the fundamental concepts, so if you do not think after her classes, you will not score well in her tests

I took her ECE311 course, and it is her first time teaching this course, the midterm and final questions are far more difficult than the previous semesters, and I don't think she teaches well in this course

Love her! Super passionate about what she does and is a great lecturer. A few of my friends and I also asked her about her research and she spent a while talking to us about the stuff she does with control theory. Definitely one of my favourite profs for second year ECE.
Very nice prof. all tests are openbook. if you read the book, answers are right there, just copy and write it down. easiest course I have ever taken.
Took the course a year ago...Great Prof.
Taught well with a small group of students. Extremely helpful and very generous with marking.
